aa(lp127
VSo today I want to talk about young people
p128
aVthrough the platform of social media.
p129
aVFirst of all, who are they? [What] do they look like?
p130
aVWell this is a girl called Guo Meimei \u2014
p131
aV20 years old, beautiful.
p132
aVShe showed off her expensive bags,
p133
aVclothes and car
p134
aVon her microblog,
p135
aVwhich is the Chinese version of Twitter.
p136
aVAnd she claimed to be the general manager of Red Cross
p137
aVat the Chamber of Commerce.
p138
aVShe didn't realize
p139
aVthat she stepped on a sensitive nerve
p140
aVand aroused national questioning,
p141
aValmost a turmoil,
p142
aVagainst the credibility of Red Cross.
p143
aVThe controversy was so heated
p144
aVthat the Red Cross had to open a press conference
p145
aVto clarify it,
p146
aVand the investigation is going on.
p147
aa(lp148
VSo far, as of today,
p149
aVwe know that she herself made up that title \u2014
p150
aVprobably because she feels proud to be associated with charity.
p151
aVAll those expensive items
p152
aVwere given to her as gifts
p153
aVby her boyfriend,
p154
aVwho used to be a board member
p155
aVin a subdivision of Red Cross at Chamber of Commerce.
