aa(lp187
VSo through microblogging,
p188
aVwe are able to understand Chinese youth even better.
p189
aVSo how are they different?
p190
aVFirst of all, most of them were born
p191
aVin the 80s and 90s,
p192
aVunder the one-child policy.
p193
aVAnd because of selected abortion
p194
aVby families who favored boys to girls,
p195
aVnow we have ended up
p196
aVwith 30 million more young men than women.
p197
aVThat could pose
p198
aVa potential danger to the society,
p199
aVbut who knows;
p200
aVwe're in a globalized world,
p201
aVso they can look for girlfriends from other countries.
p202
aVMost of them have fairly good education.
p203
aVThe illiteracy rate in China among this generation
p204
aVis under one percent.
p205
aVIn cities, 80 percent of kids go to college.
p206
aVBut they are facing an aging China
p207
aVwith a population above 65 years old
p208
aVcoming up with seven-point-some percent this year,
p209
aVand about to be 15 percent
p210
aVby the year of 2030.
p211
aVAnd you know we have the tradition
p212
aVthat younger generations support the elders financially,
p213
aVand taking care of them when they're sick.
p214
aVSo it means young couples
p215
aVwill have to support four parents
p216
aVwho have a life expectancy of 73 years old.
p217
aa(lp218
VSo making a living is not that easy
p219
aVfor young people.
p220
aVCollege graduates are not in short supply.
p221
aVIn urban areas,
p222
aVcollege graduates find the starting salary
p223
aVis about 400 U.S. dollars a month,
p224
aVwhile the average rent
p225
aVis above $500.
p226
aVSo what do they do? They have to share space \u2014
p227
aVsqueezed in very limited space
p228
aVto save money \u2014
p229
aVand they call themselves "tribe of ants."
p230
aVAnd for those who are ready to get married
p231
aVand buy their apartment,
p232
aVthey figured out they have to work
p233
aVfor 30 to 40 years
p234
aVto afford their first apartment.
p235
aVThat ratio in America
p236
aVwould only cost a couple five years to earn,
p237
aVbut in China it's 30 to 40 years
p238
aVwith the skyrocketing real estate price.
