aVMost of them don't want to go back to the countryside,
p245
aVbut they don't have the sense of belonging.
p246
aVThey work for longer hours
p247
aVwith less income, less social welfare.
p248
aVAnd they're more vulnerable
p249
aVto job losses,
p250
aVsubject to inflation,
p251
aVtightening loans from banks,
p252
aVappreciation of the renminbi,
p253
aVor decline of demand
p254
aVfrom Europe or America
p255
aVfor the products they produce.
p256
aVLast year, though,
p257
aVan appalling incident
p258
aVin a southern OEM manufacturing compound in China:
p259
aV13 young workers
p260
aVin their late teens and early 20s
